{
  "design_notes": "S0 (Intro) establishes the core drum pattern using symmetric center-lane kicks on main beats alternating with outer lane taps. S1 (Drop Build) starts by breathing heavily, dropping the event count to only two beats per bar before rising into a 4-note sweeping run that maps pitch contour to lane motion. S2 (Drop) brings the peak standard-difficulty density, featuring syncopated 0.5-beat rhythms that alternate left and right lane claps over center kicks without exceeding consecutive lane limits. S3 (Outro) provides a final high-energy burst of rapid alternating hits that tapers down to a clean, single final note on the final kick, letting the track ring out smoothly.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "S0",
      "start_bar": 0,
      "intent": "Introduce the standard alternating lane pattern and center kick anchors."
    },
    {
      "name": "S1",
      "start_bar": 1,
      "intent": "Pull back the density to breathe, followed by a dramatic sweeping build-up towards the drop."
    },
    {
      "name": "S2",
      "start_bar": 7,
      "intent": "Unleash high-density syncopated lanes matching the core synthwave drop energy."
    },
    {
      "name": "S3",
      "start_bar": 15,
      "intent": "Drive a powerful finale before tapering down to a clean, resonant finish."
    }
  ],
